The paper discusses the centrality of nodes in network topology, specifically in the context of ISP networks. This falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and system and control (cs.SY). The paper also touches on issues of security and vulnerability, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) or cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses various centrality indices and their computation, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
